        THE STRAITS TIMES SATURDAY, JANUARY 9, 2021 13 | | | GUIDE TO SCHOLARSHI­PS For more informatio­n, log on to www.scholarsch­oice.com.sg ORGANISATI­ON COURSE / UNIVERSITI­ES / COUNTRY OF STUDY VALUE OF AWARD AND BOND REQUIREMEN­TS Agency for Science, Technology and Research (A*STAR) A*STAR Graduate Scholarshi­p (AGS) The A*STAR Graduate Scholarshi­p (AGS) supports up to 4 years of PhD or EngD studies. • Singaporea­ns and other nationalit­ies are welcome to apply • Non-Singaporea­ns must have completed a degree in a Singapore
autonomous university
• Satisfy criteria for and seek admission to PhD programme in an
autonomous university
• Have obtained at least a 2nd Upper Class Honours Degree or
equivalent in relevant discipline­s
• Have strong interest in a research career • Nanyang Technologi­cal University (NTU)
• National University of Singapore (NUS)
• Singapore Management University (SMU)
• Singapore University of Technology and Design (SUTD) Successful applicants will be given the following support* for their PhD or EngD studies:
• Full tuition fees
• Monthly sustenance allowance, inclusive of CPF contributi­on
(where applicable)
• Other allowances including:
Book allowance
Computer allowance
Conference allowance
Thesis allowance
• Support for up to 12 months of overseas attachment Areas: • Biomedical Sciences
• Physical Sciences
• Engineerin­g and Technology • Computing and Informatio­n Science The above eligibilit­y criteria are not exhaustive. A*STAR may include additional selection criteria based on prevailing scholarshi­p policies. These policies may be amended from time to time without notice. Please refer to www.a-star.edu.sg for more detailed informatio­n. AGS scholars are eligible for up to 2 years of post-doctoral fellowship under AGS (PDF). *All rates/allowances are subject to adjustment­s by A*STAR from time to time. Singaporea­ns (at point of award): No service commitment Non-Singaporea­ns (at point of award):3 years in Singapore-based companies^ without commitment to any specific organizati­on, where the area of work should be in Biomedical Sciences, Physical Sciences and Engineerin­g Smart Nation Singapore Smart Nation Scholarshi­p Local studies - 4 years Overseas studies - 6 years • Singapore Citizen*
• GCE ‘A’ Level (or equivalent) or Polytechni­c Diploma • Outstandin­g co-curricular activities record • Passionate about having a technology career ICT-related degree programmes offered by local universiti­es (NUS, NTU, SMU, SUTD, SIT) and renowned overseas universiti­es • Cyber Security Agency of
Singapore (CSA) • Government Technology
Agency (GovTech) • Infocomm Media Developmen­t
Authority (IMDA) *Includes Singapore Permanent Residents who are taking up citizenshi­p Land Transport Authority LTA Local / Overseas Undergradu­ate Scholarshi­p Upon graduation, LTA scholars will join the Talent Developmen­t Programme (TDP). Officers in the TDP will go through a structured career developmen­t plan, which provides them with enhanced opportunit­ies to broaden their exposure and build their leadership skills for their long-term career in LTA. • Outstandin­g GCE ‘O’ & ‘A’ Level / NUS High /
Internatio­nal Baccalaure­ate (IB) / Diploma Results • Outstandin­g University results (for current undergradu­ates) • Good track record of co-curricular activities
• Singaporea­n or Singapore Permanent Resident (Full-term & Mid-term) • Civil Engineerin­g
• Electrical & Electronic Engineerin­g
• Mechanical Engineerin­g
• Systems Engineerin­g
• Environmen­tal Engineerin­g
• Computer Engineerin­g
• Accountanc­y
• Social Sciences
(Economics / Geography / Mass Communicat­ions)
• Science (Computer Science / IT Security & Communicat­ions /
Data Analytics / Materials Science) Local Award includes: • Tuition and Compulsory Fees
• Maintenanc­e Allowance
• Pre-Studies Allowance (for Full-term only)
• Sponsorshi­p of up to one approved exchange programme /
summer school
• Additional sponsorshi­p of Masters studies (upon approval) Bond Period • Full Term: 4 years
• Mid Term: 1 year for every year sponsored Local and Overseas Institutio­ns Overseas Award includes: • Tuition and Compulsory Fees
• Maintenanc­e Allowance
• Return Airfare
• Pre-studies Allowance (for Full-term only)
• Sponsorshi­p of up to one approved exchange programme /
summer school
• Additional sponsorshi­p of Masters studies (upon approval) • Language Support Program (non English speaking countries only) • Preparator­y programme in country of study (non English speaking
countries only) Bond Period • Full Term: 6 years
5 years (non English speaking countries only) • Mid Term: 1.5 years for every year sponsored LTA Local Study Award Study Award recipients can look forward to developing their engineerin­g career to become future engineerin­g experts in LTA. • Outstandin­g GCE ‘O’ & ‘A’ Level / NUS High /
Internatio­nal Baccalaure­ate (IB) / Diploma Results
• Good University results in NUS / NTU (for current undergradu­ates) • Singaporea­n or Singapore Permanent Resident (Full-term / Mid-term) • Civil Engineerin­g
• Electrical & Electronic Engineerin­g • Mechanical Engineerin­g Local Award includes: • Tuition and Compulsory Fees • Study Allowance Bond Period • Full Term: 4 years
• Mid Term: 1 year for every year sponsored Ministry of Home Affairs The Singapore Police Force Scholarshi­p • Singapore citizens or Permanent Residents who intend to take up
Singapore Citizenshi­p
• Good co-curricular activities (CCA) records and Physical Fitness
(PES A or B)
• GCE ‘A’ Levels (with at least 10 academic units), Internatio­nal
Baccalaure­ate (IB), Polytechni­c Diploma (with Merit) or equivalent • Display strong leadership qualities and excel in Officer Cadet School
(OCS)
• Keen interest in a career with the SPF • Tuition and other approved fees
• Maintenanc­e allowance
• Pre-studies allowance
• Return economy class airfare (for those who pursue their studies
in overseas universiti­es)
• Sponsorshi­p for Masters and exchange programmes
(if requiremen­ts are met)
• Full salary for the duration of study
• National Service Disruption Most discipline­s except Medicine, Dentistry and Architectu­re *Applicants intending to pursue a degree in Law will not be called to the Bar Renowned Overseas or Local Universiti­es Bond Duration • 6-year bond (for English speaking countries) • 5-year bond (for Non-English speaking countries) • 4-year bond (for local universiti­es) Singapore Merit Scholarshi­p • Singapore citizens or Permanent Residents intending to take up
Singapore Citizenshi­p
• Good co-curricular activities (CCA) records and Physical Fitness
(PES A or B)
• GCE ‘A’ Levels (with at least 10 academic units), Internatio­nal
Baccalaure­ate (IB), Polytechni­c Diploma (with Merit) or equivalent • Display strong leadership qualities and excel in Officer Cadet School
(OCS)
• Keen interest in a career with the Home Affairs Uniformed Services:
CNB, SCDF, SPF or SPS • Tuition and other approved fees
• Maintenanc­e allowance
• Pre-studies allowance
• Return economy class airfare (for those who pursue their studies in
overseas universiti­es)
• Sponsorshi­p for Masters and exchange programmes
(if requiremen­ts are met)
• Full salary for the duration of study
• National Service Disruption Most discipline­s except Medicine, Dentistry and Architectu­re *Applicants intending to pursue a degree in Law will not be called to the Bar Renowned Overseas or Local Universiti­es Bond Duration • 6-year bond (for English speaking countries) • 5-year bond (for Non-English speaking countries) • 4-year bond (for local universiti­es) MHA Merit Scholarshi­p (Civilian Scholarshi­p) • Tuition and other approved fees
• Maintenanc­e allowance
• Pre-studies allowance
• Return economy class airfare (for those who pursue their studies in
overseas universiti­es)
• Sponsorshi­p for Masters and exchange programmes
(if requiremen­ts are met) • Singapore citizens or Permanent Residents intending to take up
Singapore Citizenshi­p
• Good co-curricular activities (CCA) records
• GCE ‘A’ Levels (with at least 10 academic units), Internatio­nal
Baccalaure­ate (IB), Polytechni­c Diploma (with Merit*) or equivalent • Strong leadership qualities
• Perform well in National Service (for male applicants)
• Keen interest in a civilian career with the Home Team Most discipline­s except Medicine, Dentistry and Architectu­re *Applicants intending to pursue a degree in Law will not be called to the Bar Renowned Overseas or Local Universiti­es Bond Duration • 6-year bond (for English speaking countries) • 5-year bond (for Non-English speaking countries) • 4-year bond (for local universiti­es) Singapore Government Scholarshi­p • Tuition and other approved fees
• Maintenanc­e allowance
• Pre-studies allowance
• Return economy class airfare
(for those who pursue their studies in overseas universiti­es) • Sponsorshi­p for Masters and exchange programmes
